  "scientific_question": "Can the ODS perturbation loop (delta-r from physical_interaction vs coexpression_cancer layers) prospectively predict the relative efficacy ordering of drug classes in glioblastoma multiforme (GBM), BEFORE examining PRISM glioma cell viability data? Specifically: in GBM, MEK1 (+0.099) and MET (+0.185) are structural DAMPERS, while mTOR (-0.093) and EGFR (-0.111) are structural ANCHORS. This is the topology FLIP relative to NSCLC (where mTOR was the damper). ODS predicts: MEK1/MET inhibitors should outperform mTOR/EGFR inhibitors in EGFR-dependent GBM lines.",
